import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='site', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('Which variety of barley has the highest yield?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    max_yield_variety = data.loc[data['yield'].idxmax()]['variety']
    max_yield = data['yield'].max()
    plt.axhline(y=max_yield, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Yield: {max_yield:.2f} ({max_yield_variety})')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
